; maize-14: source for the mzdis truncated-tail fixture (AC6482).
;
; scripts/run-tests.ps1's mzdis_truncated test assembles this, then copies a
; truncated PREFIX of the resulting .mzb (chopping off the last 2 bytes of the
; final CP immVal instruction's 4-byte immediate) to build the actual test
; input -- byte-level truncation isn't expressible in .mazm source, so the
; harness does it directly on the assembled bytes. HALT then two harmless
; instructions decode cleanly; the final CP is where the tail gets cut.

HALT
CLR R0
CP $12345678 R0
